

2) Why Kotlin or what other the pain-points with Java the language?

  .1) NullPointerException
  .2) Verbose and boilerplate code
  .3) Mutable references and everything non-final by default
  .4) Utils everywhere
  .5) API design short-comings (You need those GoF design patterns to fill language weaknesses)
  .6) ... Rest is left for the reader after he/she begins enjoying Kotlin